<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Ethnic_groups">Ethnic groups</span></h3>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethnic_groups_in_Russia" title="Ethnic groups in Russia">Ethnic groups in Russia</a></div>
<table class="box-Expand_section plainlinks metadata ambox mbox-small-left ambox-content" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td class="mbox-image"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg" class="image"><img alt="[icon]" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png" decoding="async" width="20" height="14" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/30px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="44" data-file-height="31" /></a></td><td class="mbox-text"><div class="mbox-text-span">This section <b>needs expansion</b>. <small>You can help by <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Russia&amp;action=edit&amp;section=">adding to it</a>.</small>  <small class="date-container"><i>(<span class="date">February 2020</span>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:292px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png/290px-Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png" decoding="async" width="290" height="169" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png/435px-Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png/580px-Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png 2x" data-file-width="4836" data-file-height="2820" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ethnic_groups_in_Russia_of_more_than_1_million_people_2010_Census_English.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Ethnic groups in Russia of more than 1 million people, 2010 census</div></div></div>
<p>Ethnic <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russians" title="Russians">Russians</a> comprise 81% of the country's population.<sup id="cite_ref-perepis-2010.ru_2-3" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-perepis-2010.ru-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Russia is a multi-national state with <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ethnic_groups_in_Russia" title="List of ethnic groups in Russia">over 185 ethnic groups</a> designated as nationalities; the populations of these groups vary enormously, from millions (e.g., Russians and Tatars) to under 10,000 (e.g., <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sami_people" class="mw-redirect" title="Sami people">Samis</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eskimo" title="Eskimo">Eskimo</a>).<sup id="cite_ref-347" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-347">&#91;343&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-ethnicgroups_325-1" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-ethnicgroups-325">&#91;321&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Language">Language</span></h3>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main articles: <a href="Russian_language" title="Russian language">Russian language</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Languages_of_Russia" title="Languages of Russia">Languages of Russia</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_endangered_languages_in_Russia" title="List of endangered languages in Russia">List of endangered languages in Russia</a></div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic,_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_(en).png" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic%2C_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_%28en%29.png/220px-Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic%2C_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_%28en%29.png" decoding="async" width="220" height="138" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic%2C_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_%28en%29.png/330px-Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic%2C_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_%28en%29.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic%2C_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_%28en%29.png/440px-Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic%2C_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_%28en%29.png 2x" data-file-width="3245" data-file-height="2036" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Linguistic_map_of_the_Altaic,_Turkic_and_Uralic_languages_(en).png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Distribution of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uralic_languages" title="Uralic languages">Uralic</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Altaic_languages" title="Altaic languages">Altaic</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yukaghir_languages" title="Yukaghir languages">Yukaghir languages</a></div></div></div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png/220px-Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png" decoding="async" width="220" height="173" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png/330px-Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png/440px-Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png 2x" data-file-width="1025" data-file-height="808" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Fenno-Ugrian_languages.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Geographical distribution of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finno-Ugric_peoples" title="Finno-Ugric peoples">Finno-Ugric</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoyedic_peoples" title="Samoyedic peoples">Samoyedic peoples</a></div></div></div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg/220px-Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg.png" decoding="async" width="220" height="250" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg/330px-Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg/440px-Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="977" data-file-height="1111" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Caucasus-ethnic_en.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Languages_of_the_Caucasus" title="Languages of the Caucasus">Ethnolinguistic groups</a> in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caucasus" title="Caucasus">Caucasus</a> region</div></div></div>
<p>Russia's 185 ethnic groups speak over 100 languages.<sup id="cite_ref-britannica_18-1" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-britannica-18">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> According to the 2002 Census, 142.6&#160;million people speak Russian, followed by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tatar_language" title="Tatar language">Tatar</a> with 5.3&#160;million and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukrainian_language" title="Ukrainian language">Ukrainian</a> with 1.8&#160;million speakers.<sup id="cite_ref-348" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-348">&#91;344&#93;</a></sup> Russian is the only official state language, but the Constitution gives the individual <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republics_of_Russia" title="Republics of Russia">republics</a> the right to establish their own state languages in addition to Russian.<sup id="cite_ref-349" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-349">&#91;345&#93;</a></sup>
Despite its wide distribution, the Russian language is homogeneous throughout the country. Russian is the most geographically widespread language of Eurasia, as well as the most widely spoken <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slavic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Slavic language">Slavic language</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-350" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-350">&#91;346&#93;</a></sup> It belongs to the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indo-European_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Indo-European language">Indo-European language</a> family and is one of the living members of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Slavic_languages" title="East Slavic languages">East Slavic languages</a>, the others being <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belarusian_language" title="Belarusian language">Belarusian</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukrainian_language" title="Ukrainian language">Ukrainian</a> (and possibly <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rusyn_language" title="Rusyn language">Rusyn</a>). Written examples of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_East_Slavic" title="Old East Slavic">Old East Slavic</a> (<i>Old Russian</i>) are attested from the 10th century onwards.<sup id="cite_ref-351" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-351">&#91;347&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Russian is the second-most used language on the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet" title="Internet">Internet</a> after English,<sup id="cite_ref-352" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-352">&#91;348&#93;</a></sup> one of two official languages aboard the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Space_Station" title="International Space Station">International Space Station</a><sup id="cite_ref-353" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-353">&#91;349&#93;</a></sup> and is one of the six <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Official_languages_of_the_UN" class="mw-redirect" title="Official languages of the UN">official languages of the UN</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-354" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-354">&#91;350&#93;</a></sup> 35 languages are officially recognised in Russia in various regions by local governments.
</p>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg/220px-%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="165" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg/330px-%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg/440px-%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3264" data-file-height="2448" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:%D0%9C%D3%A9%D0%B3%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80_%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5_%D0%94%D0%B0%D2%A3%D0%B3%D1%8B%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B0%D1%802._2016.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>The Turkic-speaking <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuvans" title="Tuvans">Tuvans</a></div></div></div>
