<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Russia#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supreme_Soviet_of_Russia" title="Supreme Soviet of Russia">Supreme Soviet of the Russian SFSR</a> ratified the accords on 12 December, denouncing the 1922 treaty.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Russia#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">On 25 December, Russian SFSR was renamed the Russian Federation and the following day the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supreme_Soviet_of_the_Soviet_Union" title="Supreme Soviet of the Soviet Union">Supreme Soviet of the Soviet Union</a> ratified the accords, effectively dissolving the Soviet Union.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Areanote-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Russia#cite_ref-Areanote_9-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">When including the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_Crimea" title="Republic of Crimea">Republic of Crimea</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sevastopol" title="Sevastopol">Sevastopol</a>, the total area of Russia rises to 17,125,191&#160;km<sup>2</sup> (6,612,073&#160;sq&#160;mi)<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="Russia#cite_note-8">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Russia#cite_ref-17">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Russian&#58; <span lang="ru" title="Russian language text">Росси́йская Федера́ция</span>, <small><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romanization_of_Russian" title="Romanization of Russian">tr.</a></small> <i lang="ru-Latn" title="Russian language text">Rossiyskaya Federatsiya</i>, <small>IPA:&#160;</small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/Russian" title="Help:IPA/Russian">[rɐˈsʲijskəjə fʲɪdʲɪˈratsɨjə]</a></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-crimealanguages-363"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="Russia#cite_ref-crimealanguages_363-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Russia#cite_ref-crimealanguages_363-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annexation_of_Crimea_by_the_Russian_Federation" title="Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation">Annexed by Russia in 2014</a> Voted to join Russian Federation in 2014; recognised as a part of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine" title="Ukraine">Ukraine</a> by most of the international community.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span></h2>
<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
